[~dkavanagh]: Session stickiness still doesn't appear to be working properly.  I did the following:
I created the Duration-Based Session Stickiness
{code}
eulb-create-lb-cookie-stickiness-policy console-lb --policy-name console-sync --expiration-period 60
eulb-set-lb-policies-of-listener console-lb --lb-port 443 --policy-names console-sync
{code}
I also created the Enable Application-Controlled Session Stickiness
{code}
eulb-create-app-cookie-stickiness-policy console-lb -p console-sync-cookie -c console-sync
eulb-set-lb-policies-of-listener console-lb --lb-port 443 --policy-names console-sync-cookie
{code}
I then upgraded one console and left the other the older version.  The problem still persists.  The UI is still unstable/unusable.  I still have to upgrade eucaconsole on both instances for the problem to go away.
